nages and this individual will eventually accept the child back.   But while they are there, the HMBT Sisters care for them completely.\r\n\r\nOn a typical day they will arise at 5:30-6:00 am.  After eating breakfast they will get dressed and ready for school which  goes till the early afternoon.   At Sahar the school is within the orphanage house itself;  at Merces-Giriz the kids take a bus or walk to nearby independent schools.   In the mid-afternoon there is additonal tutoring by a paid teacher at Sahar and by volunteer local college students at Merces-Giriz.  In the late afternoon the kids all do homework,  chores, have play time,  take baths, eat dinner and have prayer time.  They typically go to bed around 9 pm.    On Sundays, there is extra time for watching T.V.,  having a party, music, dance,  and also visits by family members or persons from the community.\r\n\r\nOn this page you will find some profiles typical of the orphans.','Orphan Profiles','','inherit','open','open','','151-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:28:43','2014-03-13 02:28:43','',151,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/151-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(385,1,'2014-03-13 02:32:15','2014-03-13 02:32:15','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-374 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" alt=\"DSC01136 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                                                                                                                                                               Gauri Shetty</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                     Tulsi Shetty</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tulsi was born November 2003 and her sister Gauri was born April 2005.  Both are living at the Sahar Orphanage.  They are in 3rd and 2nd standard respectively.  Their mother died in a road accident.  Their father had no job and was homeless so he brought the girls to the orphanage.   He hopes to collect them after they complete school through the 7th standard at Sahar,  by which time he hopes his personal situation will have improved.</p>','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:32:15','2014-03-13 02:32:15','',162,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/162-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(404,1,'2014-03-13 13:18:28','2014-03-13 13:18:28','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-374 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" alt=\"DSC01136 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                                                                                                                                                                     Gauri</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                          Tulsi</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tulsi was born November 2003 and her sister Gauri was born April 2005.  Both are living at the Sahar Orphanage.  They are in 3rd and 2nd standard respectively.  Their mother died in a road accident.  Their father had no job and was homeless so he brought the girls to the orphanage.   He hopes to collect them after they complete school through the 7th standard at Sahar,  by which time he hopes his personal situation will have improved.</p>','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 13:18:28','2014-03-13 13:18:28','',162,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/162-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(386,1,'2014-03-13 02:32:45','2014-03-13 02:32:45','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-374 alignleft\" alt=\"DSC01134 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01134-Custom.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"320\" /></a>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-375\" alt=\"DSC01136 (Custom)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01136-Custom.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                                                                                                                                                               Gauri Shetty</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                     Tulsi Shetty</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tulsi was born November 2003 and her sister Gauri was born April 2005.  Both are living at the Sahar Orphanage.  They are in 3rd and 2nd standard respectively.  Their mother died in a road accident.  Their father had no job and was homeless so he brought the girls to the orphanage.   He hopes to collect them after they complete school through the 7th standard at Sahar,  by which time he hopes his personal situation will have improved.</p>','Tulsi & Gauri Shetty','','inherit','open','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:32:45','2014-03-13 02:32:45','',162,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/162-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2014-03-13 02:37:15','2014-03-13 02:37:15','','Bios','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:37:15','2014-03-13 02:37:15','',7,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/7-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(388,1,'2014-03-13 02:37:35','2014-03-13 02:37:35','<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01043-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-257\" alt=\"DSC01043 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01043-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sr. Paulette comes from a Christian Indian family from the island of Mauritus.  In her youth she decided to become a nun and came to Calcutta to join Mother Teresa.  For about 20 years she worked with Mother Teresa mainly helping women and children and doing family planning work.  She developed a severe back condition which required hospitalization. She was sent to a Mumbai hospital where she spent several months.  When she emerged from recuperation Mother Teresa urged her to remain in Mumbai in a life of service.  This is how, in 1989,  she became the foundress of a new order of nuns called the Handmaids of the Blessed Trinity.  Today the order contains about 40 nuns;  about 10 of these are directly working with Sr. Paulette at the orphanages.</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Sister Paulette','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:37:35','2014-03-13 02:37:35','',25,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/25-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(389,1,'2014-03-13 02:37:53','2014-03-13 02:37:53','<p dir=\"ltr\">Sister Eliza with Muskan<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01196-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-236\" alt=\"DSC01196 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01196-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sister Eliza comes from a Christian Indian family in Goa.  She came to Mumbai to study Social Work.  She completed college and a M.A. degree in Social Work.  She was very much drawn to helping the abandoned and poor.  During this time, around 1990,  she was introduced to Sr. Paulette and became the first Sister to join the HMBT.  For more than 20 years now she has been a strong pillar to the order.  Today she spends most of her time running the day to day affairs of the Sahar Orphanage.  She also teaches at a nearby private school,  and through this employment,  brings in financial support to run the orphanage.</p>\r\n&nbsp;','Sister Eliza','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-v1','','','2014-03-13 02:37:53','2014-03-13 02:37:53','',23,'http://handmaids-local/uncategorized/23-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(390,1,'2014-03-13 02:38:16','2014-03-13 02:38:16','<p dir=\"ltr\">Sister Eliza with Muskan<a href=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01196-Small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-236\" alt=\"DSC01196 (Small)\" src=\"http://www.vitalypeker.com/handmaids/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/DSC01196-Small.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sister Eliza comes from a Christian Indian family in Goa.  She came to Mumbai to study Social Work.  She completed college and a M.A. degree in Social Work.  She was very much drawn to helping the abandoned and poor.  During this time, around 1990,  she was introduced to Sr. Paulette and became the first 